# Source of truth for the SERVING / EVAL / LOAD-TEST Python stack.
# This is what the backend Docker image and the CTranslate2 eval path need.
# Pin major versions here; run pip-compile to resolve exact versions:
#   pip-compile requirements/requirements.in -o requirements/requirements.txt --resolver=backtracking
# Python 3.10 only.
#
# NOTE: fairseq + ai4bharat-transliteration are NOT here on purpose. The serving
# engine is CTranslate2, which does not import fairseq. The fairseq/ai4bharat
# stack is only needed offline (baseline eval + dictionary precompute) and lives
# in requirements/requirements-precompute.in, which is deliberately not
# pip-compiled because urduhack pins tensorflow-datasets~=3.1 / tf2crf and the
# fairseq sdist has a broken PEP 517 build. See that file for install steps.

# --- Serving ---
fastapi>=0.110,<0.116
uvicorn[standard]>=0.29,<0.35
pydantic>=2.5,<3.0
pydantic-settings>=2.1,<3.0

# --- Model runtime (CTranslate2 INT8) ---
ctranslate2>=4.0,<5.0
sentencepiece>=0.1.99,<0.3

# --- Dictionary / cache ---
marisa-trie>=1.1,<2.0

# --- Load testing ---
locust>=2.24,<3.0

# --- Evaluation (optional LLM-as-judge only) ---
openai>=1.30,<2.0

# --- Numerics (kept <2 for broader compatibility) ---
numpy<2

